    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Montreal</placeName>
                <date>19th April 5624</date>
            </p>
            <p>Dear Sir—</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I only received yours of<lb/>
                <date>12th</date>, this morning—it has been<lb/> detained fully four days. Had
                I<lb/> received it earlier, I should have <lb/>sent a reply at once asking you<lb/>
                to send <del>fr</del> the books. As it is,<lb/> their sale will be <sic>spoilt</sic>
                till<lb/> the fall holy days. You can however<lb/> send them at once at the
                prices<lb/> named—and bound. There may<lb/> perhaps be a call for a couple of<lb/>
                sets on <add>שבועות</add>, tho' I doubt this.<lb/> As I shall then not be able to
                sell<lb/> till the time mentioned, I may make<lb/> you wait for your money till
                I<lb/> collect it in <placeName>New York</placeName> where it is<lb/> due me. I have
                had to lose considerably<lb/> by sending books to <placeName>New York</placeName>
                when</p>
            <p rend="The following is written sideways in the left margin">My kind regards to
                    <persName>Miss <sic>Grats</sic></persName> when you see her. S. O. P.</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>bills were at par, I foolishly<lb/> refrained from drawing,<lb/> at the time,
                    <add>וזה שכרי</add>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">By the way, will you please tell me<lb/> whether
                    <persName>Cohen</persName> of the “Record” is in<lb/> your estimation likely to
                pay<lb/> an amount of about $100 he owes<lb/> me for books—most of which<lb/> he
                ordered during the past year<lb/>—some were Catechisms for the<lb/> Sunday School
                    <add>?</add> in<lb/>
                <placeName>New York</placeName>. Of course this is<lb/> entirely <add>דינינו</add>.
                Have you<lb/> found him prompt?—for I<lb/> presume he has had books from you.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I shall write to inform<lb/>
                <persName>Mr. Joseph</persName> what you write<lb/> about the Bibles. They are<lb/>
                no doubt at his agents, for</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>it was only yesterday (<date>18th</date>) we were<lb/> speaking about them, as he
                happened<lb/> to be here on a visit.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">What you write about <persName>Mrs<lb/> Nadper</persName> surprises
                me very much—<lb/>for I had always been accustomed<lb/> to pay <persName>Mr J. H.
                    Joseph</persName> my sum<lb/> I received for you. I was fully<lb/> aware
                    <persName>Mrs Nadper</persName> paid me—though<lb/> forget the sum &amp; date. I
                think<lb/> I shall find I paid it to <persName>Mr Joseph</persName>,<lb/> but shall
                look into it. I must<lb/> wait till after <add>פסח</add> to write you<lb/> again,
                for I have not an hours leisure<lb/> that I see before me. I have just<lb/> been
                requested to give the annual<lb/> address at the Convocation of Mc<lb/> Gill
                University, I cannot refuse</p>
            <pb n="4"/>
            <p>—it takes place on <date>third May</date>,<lb/> I have examinations, and<lb/> now
                every day Synagogue duties<lb/> that will occupy me for 9 days<lb/>—besides a review
                of a review<lb/> of <persName>Renau</persName> on the analogies of the<lb/> Semitic
                languages &amp; the <hi rend="underline">Iroquois</hi><lb/> &amp; <hi
                    rend="underline">Algonquia</hi>! My answer is<lb/> to <persName>N. O.</persName>
                a priest of the seminary<lb/> here, who writes anonymously<lb/>—and a fellow student
                of <persName>Renau</persName>.<lb/> I write (also anonymously) at<lb/> the request
                of <persName>Dr Danhou<add>?</add></persName> who is not<lb/> “up” in the Semitic
                languages—and the<lb/> part which he has already seen of<lb/> the manner I handle
                the priest has<lb/> given him not a little amusement.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">But I must close. If you<lb/> could only see how I am writing in
                the<lb/> midst of scrubbing “preparing for <date>Pesach</date>”<lb/> you would say I
                must be a very determined<lb/> fellow. <add>מועדים לשמחה</add> Muchos
                    <sic>annos</sic><lb/> y buenos.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Yours truly</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <persName role="author">Abraham de Sola</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="The following is written sideways at the left side of the page">I will send you
                the continuation of the Biography after the Holy days<lb/> Please let me hear soon
                from you, &amp; it seems well perhaps to send<lb/> the books soon, on account of use
                &amp; rate of exchange. Where gold was 90 in <placeName>New York</placeName><lb/> a
                draft on <placeName>N. Y.</placeName> was worth 65 here.<lb/> i.e 35 to 40
                discourse</p>
        </body>
